2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 352
BY REPRESENTATIVE KERNER
RETIREMENT/TEACHERS: Creates a task force to study the Optional Retirement Plan
within the Teachers' Retirement System of Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To establish a task force to study the Optional Retirement Plan within the Teachers'
3 Retirement System of Louisiana, including differences affecting long-term
4 participants, and to report its findings to the House Committee on Retirement no
5 later than ninety days prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular Session of the
6 Legislature.
7 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana recognizes
8 that the Optional Retirement Plan (ORP) was created to provide flexibility and to assist in
9 the recruitment and retention of faculty and staff within public postsecondary education
10 institutions; and
11 WHEREAS, the legislature created the ORP as a defined contribution plan within
12 the Teachers' Retirement System of Louisiana (TRSL); the traditional TRSL plan is a
13 defined benefit plan with a guaranteed pension, but the ORP is a defined contribution plan
14 without a guaranteed pension and participants assume all investment risks, making the ORP
15 unique among the plans available to public employees in Louisiana; and
16 WHEREAS, ORP participants are not provided Social Security coverage, resulting
17 an in increased reliance on individual retirement savings; and
18 WHEREAS, employer contribution rates for ORP participants in Louisiana is
19 currently 6.2% of pay; and
20 WHEREAS, the median default employer contribution rate for optional defined
21 contribution plan accounts is 8.25% of pay according to National Association of State
